main event: A UFO was observed over Lake Melissa, Minnesota on August 30, 1965, which was later identified as possibly being a satellite.
interesting points: The sighting occurred at night and lasted for about 5 minutes., The object exhibited erratic, bobbing motion similar to that of a satellite., The report indicated the object was comparable in brightness to the planet Venus., A later analysis suggested it was likely the SATI ID JOHN-15 satellite passing overhead., The report was responded to by a Lieutenant Colonel of the USAF.
witness description: The witnesses stated that the bright light traveled at high speed and was unlike any known aircraft.
